coursework an open source course management system coursework open source initiative in june 2003 stanford university announced the open source release of its course management system coursework since this open source release of coursework stanford university has joined forces with three other institutions the university of michigan indiana university and mit to develop a new collaboration and learning environment this community source software development effort called the sakai project aims to create open source course management tools and related software for the higher education community with stanford's participation in the sakai project further development on the open source release of coursework version 3.0 has ceased and will no longer be made available for additional information including instructions on how to download the sakai code please go to the sakai project web site at http www sakaiproject org stanford academic computing a division of stanford university libraries and academic information resources helpsu copyright 2004 by the board of trustees of the leland stanford junior university
